<img loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-1438349 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="719" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342.jpg 678w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/images.jpeg-342-600x337.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />Two female hawkers were on Friday crushed to death by a truck around Lotto, inbound Lagos on the Lagos-Ibadan expressway. Mr Babatunde Akinbiyi, the Spokesman, Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Corps (TRACE), confirmed the incident to News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Abeokuta. Akinbiyi explained that the incident occurred around 3:30pm, saying that the driver of the truck, marked SMK 82 XY, lost control, skidded off the road and rammed into two female road-side hawkers, killing them on the spot. The TRACE spokesman stated that three other people were injured in the accident. Akinbiyi  said “the truck has been taken to Mowe Divisional Police Station, with the driver in their custody.” He said that the deceased were deposited at the Idera morgue in Sagamu while the injured were taken to Famobis hospital, Mowe. He commiserated with the family of the deceased, while urging motorists to avoid excessive speeding and reckless driving on the road.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .